      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## Features\n\n* **Japanese translation support** — thanks to @GennoBou ([#188](https://github.com/trganda/obsidian-attachment-management/pull/188))\n* **Typed i18n** — `t()` keys, placeholders, and parameter names are now type-checked against the English locale; `zh.ts`/`ja.ts` are constrained with `LocaleShape<typeof en>` so missing/extra/typo'd keys fail at compile time ([#212](https://github.com/trganda/obsidian-attachment-management/pull/212))\n* **Attachment Path validator** — empty values, illegal filename characters, and unknown `${variable}` tokens are flagged inline in the setting tab ([#212](https://github.com/trganda/obsidian-attachment-management/pull/212))\n\n## Bug Fixes\n\n* `${date}` is now anchored to the attachment's `stat.ctime` instead of `moment()`, so re-arranges and re-renames stay idempotent and no longer reroll the date portion of filenames ([#212](https://github.com/trganda/obsidian-attachment-management/pull/212))\n\n## Internal\n\n* Prune unused i18n keys, merge the `notifications` block into `notices`, and route the remaining hardcoded `new Notice(...)` strings through `t()`\n* Translate i18n module comments to English; tidy `package.json`\n\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/trganda/obsidian-attachment-management/compare/0.11.2...0.12.0",
